---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout title="Mohammed's Blog | Books" description="Mohammed's Books">
	<section id="books">
		<div class="wrapper">
			<div class="book">
				<header>
					<div class="book-title">Rust Programming for Beginners</div>
					<button
						id="toggleSidebar"
						class="toggle-sidebar"
						aria-label="Toggle sidebar">&#9776; Menu</button
					>
				</header>

				<div class="container">
					<nav id="sidebar">
						<ul class="toc">
							<li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
							<li>
								<a href="#basics">Basics</a>
								<ul>
									<li>
										<a href="#getting-started"
											>Getting Started</a
										>
									</li>
									<li><a href="#examples">Examples</a></li>
								</ul>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</nav>
					<main>
						<section id="introduction">
							<h2>Introduction</h2>
							<p>
								This section introduces the Rust programming
								language, covering its history, core philosophy,
								and the reasons it has become a favorite among
								systems programmers. Learn why Rust offers a
								unique approach to system level development,
								balancing speed, safety, and concurrency.
							</p>
						</section>

						<section id="basics">
							<h2>Basics</h2>
							<p>
								Understanding the fundamentals of Rust is
								crucial for any beginner. This section provides
								an overview of basic syntax, control flows, data
								types, and the ownership model that defines
								memory management in Rust.
							</p>
							<section id="getting-started">
								<h3>Getting Started</h3>
								<p>
									Set up your Rust environment, write your
									first Rust program, and learn how to compile
									and run it. This segment makes sure you have
									all the tools you need to start programming
									with Rust.
								</p>
							</section>
							<section id="examples">
								<h3>Examples</h3>
								<p>
									Review detailed examples that illustrate how
									to use Rust's syntax in different scenarios.
									Each example is explained to ensure you
									understand the practices that make Rust
									unique and effective.
								</p>
							</section>
						</section>
					</main>
				</div>

				<footer>
					<p>&copy; Learn Rust</p>
				</footer>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
	.container {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	header {
		background: #f7e6d5;
		padding: 10px 20px;
		text-align: center;
		border-bottom: 2px solid #d3c1b1;
	}

	header .book-title {
		font-size: 24px;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	#sidebar {
		flex: 1 1 250px;
		background: #dcd0c0;
		padding: 20px;
		height: auto;
		overflow-y: auto;
	}

	.toc li {
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.toc a {
		color: #5c4b37;
		text-decoration: none;
		display: block;
		transition: color 0.3s;
	}

	.toc a:hover {
		color: #312920;
	}

	.toc ul {
		padding-left: 20px;
	}

	main {
		flex: 10 1 60%;
		padding: 20px;
		background: #fbf0e4;
	}

	h2 {
		border-bottom: 1px solid #d3c1b1;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.container {
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		#sidebar,
		main {
			flex-basis: 100%;
		}
	}

	footer {
		background: #f7e6d5;
		text-align: center;
		padding: 10px 20px;
		border-top: 2px solid #d3c1b1;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: #5c4b37;
	}

	footer p {
		margin: 0;
	}
</style>
